gomodel:SYNGO_420  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1 colocalization of CDKL5 with PSD-95, coimmunoprecipitation of CDKL5 with PSD-95 but not with Synaptophysin.\nFig. 3 localization of CDKL5 to synapses depend on PSD-95\nFig. S2 CDKL5 is enriched in the PSD fraction\n\n14/4/2017 Pim\nFig.S1 (binding of recombinant PSD-95 and CDKL5) shows that the interaction of these proteins is direct. This places CDKL5 in the same cellular compartment as PSD-95 --> postsynapse.. Experimental description: Experiments with coltured neurons and biochemical analisys are form rat. These experiments are featured in Fig. 1, 3 and S2.\n\nLiteral from M&M\n\"Cell Cultures and Transfection. Cultures of cortical neurons were\nprepared from E18 Sprague-Dawley (SD) rat\"\n\"Affinity Purification of CDKL5-Interacting Proteins. Rat synaptosomes\nwere purified according to the procedures described previously\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_420" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

